The paper discusses the mobility patterns and social ties in intermittently connected wireless networks, which are typical topics in the computer science sub-categories of networked and mobile systems (cs.NI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The proposed technique involves designing new prediction metrics, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the efficiency of communication protocols, which could be related to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NIA).
